OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO COMMERCIAL LAW -- GENERAL REGULATORY PROVISIONS --
CONSUMER PROTECTION FROM INDEMNIFIED (LIABILITY-FREE) PRODUCTS ACT
***
1 This act would prohibit mandating indemnified products to consumers where a refusal or
2 acceptance would result in loss of employment, loss of employment opportunity, loss of promotion,
3 loss of the ability to receive a private or public education, or coercion or harassment if a consumer
4 declines an indemnified product.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
